  <abstract>Stereograph print of Ashwood Hall, Home of Leonidas Polk and Andrew Polk, located in Columbia. Several people are standing outside the home. The home has full-length windows, Corinthian columns, a triangular pediment, and iron railing.</abstract>
  <abstract>Ashwood Hall, known as the Marble Mansion, was built for Bishop Leonidas Polk in the 1830's. The house was later sold to Andrew Jackson Polk, who had the home expanded. The home was destroyed by a fire in 1874.</abstract>
